&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="refbegin columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;">\n<p><span id="cnote_a"><b><a href="#ref_a">^</a></b></span>&#160;<b>a:</b>&#160;See the article <a href="/wiki/Society_of_the_Song_Dynasty" class="mw-redirect" title="Society of the Song Dynasty">Society of the Song Dynasty</a>.<br />\n<span id="cnote_b"><b><a href="#ref_b">^</a></b></span>&#160;<b>b:</b>&#160;Refer to the <i>Partisans and factions, reformers and conservatives</i> section of the article <a href="/wiki/History_of_the_Song_Dynasty" class="mw-redirect" title="History of the Song Dynasty">History of the Song Dynasty</a>.<br />\n<span id="cnote_c"><b><a href="#ref_c">^</a></b></span>&#160;<b>c:</b>&#160;From his biography in the <i>Dictionary of Scientific Biography</i> (New York 1970\xe2\x80\x931990)<br />\n<span id="cnote_d"><b><a href="#ref_d">^</a></b></span>&#160;<b>d:</b>&#160;For more, see <a href="/wiki/Architecture_of_the_Song_Dynasty" class="mw-redirect" title="Architecture of the Song Dynasty">Architecture of the Song Dynasty</a>.<br />\n<span id="cnote_g"><b><a href="#ref_g">^</a></b></span>&#160;<b>g:</b>&#160;For deforestation due to the Song Dynasty iron industry and efforts to curb it, refer to <a href="/wiki/Economy_of_the_Song_Dynasty" class="mw-redirect" title="Economy of the Song Dynasty">Economy of the Song Dynasty</a><br />\n<span id="cnote_h"><b><a href="#ref_h">^</a></b></span>&#160;<b>h:</b>&#160;Zhang\'s biography on Shen is of great importance as it contains\xe2\x80\x94according to the historian <a href="/wiki/Nathan_Sivin" title="Nathan Sivin">Nathan Sivin</a> \xe2\x80\x94 the fullest and most accurate account of Shen Kuo\'s life.<sup id="cite_ref-sivin_1995_III_49_168-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-sivin_1995_III_49-168">[168]</a></sup><br /></p>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Shen_Kuo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Citations">Citations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Shen_Kuo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Citations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-yao_2003_544-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-yao_2003_544_1-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-yao_2003_544_1-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-yao_2003_544_1-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-yao_2003_544_1-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Yao (2003), 544.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-needham_1986_volume_4_part_2_33-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-needham_1986_volume_4_part_2_33_2-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-needham_1986_volume_4_part_2_33_2-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Needham (1986), Volume 4, Part 2, 33.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Makeham2008-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Makeham2008_3-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">John Makeham (2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=TQ4NAQAAMAAJ&amp;focus=searchwithinvolume&amp;q=essays"><i>China: The World\'s Oldest Living Civilization Revealed</i></a>. Thames &amp; Hudson. p.&#160;239. <a href="/wiki/International_Stan